    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "thanks. i'll try the feathering thing. what about the corners? i'm worried about getting those inside corners to look smooth without getting a huge buildup of mud in the crease. should i use a different tool or just be more careful?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Inside corners are tricky, but using a wide taping knife while applying the mud is your best bet. Start by pressing the tape securely into the corner, then use a long, flexible knife to apply the mud in a sweeping motion, keeping the pressure light to avoid pushing excess material into the crease. Feathering out the mud *beyond* the corner line will help it blend smoothly into the adjacent walls.",
