    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "got it. one more thing, i noticed some small gaps or little holes where the drywall meets the studs in a couple of spots. is it better to just fill them with more mud or should i be worried about something else?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "For small gaps and pinholes where the drywall meets the studs, a small amount of joint compound applied with a putty knife is usually sufficient. If the holes are very small, you can often just press a dab of mud into them and then feather it out with a thin coat. However, if the gaps are large or seem structural, you might want to inspect them to ensure there isn't an underlying issue before just filling them in.",
      "source": "target",
